{"tid":1929144,"cid":18,"subCid":0,"title":"統一叫法：我地係Hongkonger","createTime":"2020-03-16T19:09:12.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-18T15:44:41.000Z","uid":305607,"like":51,"dislike":5,"uniUserReply":28,"replies":[{"pid":"5855b9b1ad2789fc5d3d6648f6ecf9fa7983659d","tid":1929144,"uid":305607,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T19:09:12.000Z","msg":"如題，見到大部分地方都寫Hongkonger，但有時都仲見到Hongkongese。係時候統一叫法，叫返自己做Hongkonger。<br />\n<br />\n以小弟所理解，讀音為hong-kon-ner，無g音嘅，有錯請指正。"},{"pid":"94406e046a88fe34d0aecde556c1167034fb5883","tid":1929144,"uid":164153,"like":2,"dislike":27,"score":-25,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T19:12:25.000Z","msg":"Kongese 會唔會好啲"},{"pid":"53dc5b94539f9cb69050e92f7ee64d0813c59360","tid":1929144,"uid":12185,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T19:13:04.000Z","msg":"Gchi"},{"pid":"9155a3e10ea0c1be0b55a8e4681b3beabbe0bc16","tid":1929144,"uid":165683,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T19:21:46.000Z","msg":"Push"},{"pid":"8cc7401eea956a6bc6790ad7aa4f255c4c78d9d6","tid":1929144,"uid":345819,"like":2,"dislike":17,"score":-15,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T19:34:25.000Z","msg":"Hong Kongese係形容詞<br />\n平時見nationality ethnicity可以填<br />\n例句I&rsquo;m Hong Kongese<br />\n<br />\nHongkonger 係noun<br />\n例句I&rsquo;m a Hongkonger<br />\n<br />\n情況有啲似British同Briton嘅分別"},{"pid":"1e2d84d6989d1039a6becf57bfc49ec61e3a96c0","tid":1929144,"uid":345819,"like":7,"dislike":4,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-16T19:47:14.000Z","msg":"個人覺得用Hong Kongese可以加強身份認同同話俾外國人聽原來除咗Chinese仲有Hong Kongese, Taiwanese，幾個相提並論就突顯到分別<br />\n<br />\n不過而家呢個identity 仲未國際間普及<br />\n好多人仲係就咁用Hong Kong 嚟形容<br />\n有啲似New Zealand (n/adj) 同New Zealander <br />\n例如講香港教育制度仲係用the Hong Kong education system，其實可以用the Hong Kongese education system<br />\n<br />\n至於Hongkonger 自己覺得有陣都市味，usage覺得可以睇下New Yorker"},{"pid":"646e38734eb8d0393fdcf78fb47baa6f08108279","tid":1929144,"uid":14119,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"